expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2327</fr:anchor><fr:addr>hodge-theory-iii-7.1.2</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-7.1.2.xml</fr:route><fr:number>7.1.2</fr:number><fr:parent>hodge-theory-iii-7.1</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>
    A filtered quasi-isomorphism <fr:tex>u\colon (K,F)\to (K',F')</fr:tex> induces an isomorphism of spectral sequences <fr:tex>u\colon  E_\bullet ^{\bullet \bullet }(K,F)\to  E_\bullet ^{\bullet \bullet }(K',F')</fr:tex>.
    An object <fr:tex>K</fr:tex> of <fr:tex>\operatorname {D}^+\operatorname {F}\mathscr {A}</fr:tex> thus defines a spectral sequence <fr:tex>E_\bullet ^{\bullet \bullet }(K)</fr:tex>.
    
    Similarly, an object <fr:tex>L</fr:tex> of <fr:tex>\operatorname {D}^+\operatorname {F}_2\mathscr {A}</fr:tex> defines an accumulation of spectral sequences of the type considered in <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-ii-1.4.9"
href="hodge-theory-ii-1.4.9.xml"
number="1.4.9"></fr:ref>.
  </fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
